RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 5F Turf CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 70000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For Less Than $30,000 In Their Last 3 Starts). (If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the Tapeta Course at Five Furlongs) (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEACHLAND tracked in the three path, was nudged along inside of foes around the turn, ridden from the two path into the lane, rallied past an outer trio into the final furlong, and drew clear. UP FOR IT bumped with an outer foe at the start, rated in the four path, tipped to the three path early around the turn, was roused while shifting out to the six path turning into the lane, and ran on for place. OOLONG HAI (IRE) was sent to set the pace inside of rivals in the two path, cued while tipping out to the four path turning into the stretch, began to fade after the eighth pole, but held show. MYSTIC SUNRISE trailed in the four path, merged into the two path and was roused early around the turn, but was carried out to the nine path turning into the stretch, stayed on, but just missed getting up for minor placings. SICKLE DANCE bumped with an inner foe at the start, prompted the pace in the four path, was under coaxing in the three path passing the quarter, floated out to the five path at the top of the stretch, but had to steady just after the eighth pole, and flattened. GOLDEN STAR pressed in the five path, was driven in the four path around the turn, floated out to the eight path going into the stretch, and weakened.

ENTRY.COMMENT: trail4p,roused2p around turn,carried9p into lane,stayed on,miss

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 9 5F Turf CR: 85. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 71000. FOR TWO YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR RESTRICTED OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $75,000. Weight, 120 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Claiming Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $75,000. (If deemed inadvisable to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the Tapeta Course at Five Furlongs) (Rail at 24 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ESPERON set the pace in the two path, was cued midway around the turn, dug in from the two path into the stretch, but began to drift out in the final furlong, bumped an outer foe after a left handed cue around the final sixteenth, and just held on. OKIRO bumped with an outer foe at the start, stalked inside, was roused along the rail rounding the turn, tipped out to the three path to bid at the top of the stretch, ran on, but got herded out around the eighth pole and bumped at the sixteenth to finish with place. KING OF THE TRACK tracked in the two path, was coaxed passing the quarter, floated out to the five path in upper stretch, and kept on for show. RUNNIN' ROCKET bumped with an inner foe at the start, rated in the three path, was cued passing the quarter, shifted out to the six path under a drive in upper stretch, and kicked on. KING SKULL trailed in the two path, was driven around the turn, angled out to the nine path in upper stretch, but made no impact. SPIRIT'S MISCHIEF vied for the lead in the three path, was put to coaxing early around the turn, but failed to respond, and faded in the stretch. PRIVATE THOUGHTS chased in the four path, was ridden from the two path into the stretch, and did not threaten. SHEA D WORLD pressed in the five path, floated out to the seven path turning into the lane, and yielded. AFTER AN OBJECTION LODGED BY THE RIDER OF OKIRO AGAINST THE RIDER OF ESPERON AS WELL AS A STEWARDS INQUIRY, ESPERON WAS DISQUALIFIED FROM FIRST AN PLACED SECOND FOR DRIFTING OUT AND BUMPING OKIRO INSIDE THE FINAL FURLONG IMPEDING OKIRO FROM A FAIR CHANCE TO GET BY.
